        </div>
      </li>
      
      <li class="ctsh clearfix" data-cid="20635828">
        <div class="ilst">
          <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/jimmyraynor/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u50728457-4.jpg" alt="NewmanLoathesU" class="" /></a>
        </div>
        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/20635828/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/20635828/" class="">第150页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/jimmyraynor/" class=" " title="NewmanLoathesU">NewmanLoathesU</a>
                (Hello, Jerry.)
              
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="20635828">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">这是Oxford出版的原书（纯英文原版）的第6页上的一段话：

 But think instead about some
of the regimes that rose and fell in the last century: think about the
Nazi regime in Germany and the 6 million Jews who were killed by
it, or think about Mao’s China and the 20 million or more who died
as a result of the famine induced by the so-called ‘Great Leap
Forward’. Meanwhile in other countries ...</span>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/20635828/">(<span class="">1回应</span>)</a>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2012-08-26 05:30</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                这是Oxford出版的原书（纯英文原版）的第6页上的一段话：<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q> But think instead about some
of the regimes that rose and fell in the last century: think about the
Nazi regime in Germany and the 6 million Jews who were killed by
it, or think about Mao’s China and the 20 million or more who died
as a result of the famine induced by the so-called ‘Great Leap
Forward’. Meanwhile in other countries whole populations saw
their living standards rise at an unprecedented rate. </q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>这是译林出版社出的通识读本上全书第150页（英文部分第6页）上对应的一段话：<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><blockquote><q>But think instead about some
of the regimes that rose and fell in the last century: think about the
Nazi regime in Germany and the 6 million Jews who were killed by
it. Meanwhile in other countries whole populations saw
their living standards rise at an unprecedented rate. </q></blockquote><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>咦，看起来完全一样不是吗？
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







<div class="rec-sec">

    <span class="rec">

<a href="https://www.douban.com/accounts/register?reason=collect" class="j a_show_login lnk-sharing lnk-douban-sharing">推荐</a>
</span>
</div>

                  </div>
                <div class="pl col-time">
                  <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/20635828/#comments">1回应</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
                  2012-08-26 05:30
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  

